race.comment: Tough race. KILLENAULE (2) was okay at his Australian debut at Ararat over 1300m, finding them a bit sharp after getting back in the run. Stepping out in trip now is a big tick for him and his jumpouts suggested he's acclimatised well. He can improve. SHARE THE PENNIES (10) has been good in two runs back and should be peaking out to a mile now.  The winkers go on for the first time and Bates has options from the draw. She can put her best foot forward. NIGHTOWL (3) was just fair at his Australian debut but this is easier and his NZ form prior was solid. EPOCH (1) finished off nicely off a short break at Werribee and can only be better for that effort.
